{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"How does the news shape the way we see the world?"},{"time":4000,"text":"Here's the world based on the way it looks -- based on landmass."},{"time":10000,"text":"And here's how news shapes what Americans see."},{"time":17000,"text":"This map -- (Applause) -- this map shows the number of seconds"},{"time":31000,"text":"that American network and cable news organizations dedicated to news stories,"},{"time":36000,"text":"by country, in February of 2007 -- just one year ago."},{"time":41000,"text":"Now, this was a month when North Korea agreed to dismantle its nuclear facilities."},{"time":47000,"text":"There was massive flooding in Indonesia."},{"time":51000,"text":"And in Paris, the IPCC released its study confirming man's impact on global warming."},{"time":59000,"text":"The U.S. accounted for 79 percent of total news coverage."},{"time":64000,"text":"And when we take out the U.S. and look at the remaining 21 percent,"},{"time":69000,"text":"we see a lot of Iraq -- that's that big green thing there -- and little else."},{"time":76000,"text":"The combined coverage of Russia, China and India, for example, reached just one percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"When we analyzed all the news stories and removed just one story,"},{"time":90000,"text":"here's how the world looked."},{"time":92000,"text":"What was that story? The death of Anna Nicole Smith."},{"time":99000,"text":"This story eclipsed every country except Iraq,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and received 10 times the coverage of the IPCC report."},{"time":108000,"text":"And the cycle continues;"},{"time":110000,"text":"as we all know, Britney has loomed pretty large lately."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113000,"text":"So, why don't we hear more about the world?"},{"time":116000,"text":"One reason is that news networks have reduced the number of their foreign bureaus by half."},{"time":122000,"text":"Aside from one-person ABC mini-bureaus in Nairobi, New Delhi and Mumbai,"},{"time":131000,"text":"there are no network news bureaus in all of Africa, India or South America"},{"time":139000,"text":"-- places that are home to more than two billion people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"The reality is that covering Britney is cheaper."},{"time":150000,"text":"And this lack of global coverage is all the more disturbing"},{"time":153000,"text":"when we see where people go for news."},{"time":156000,"text":"Local TV news looms large,"},{"time":160000,"text":"and unfortunately only dedicates 12 percent of its coverage to international news."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165000,"text":"And what about the web?"},{"time":167000,"text":"The most popular news sites don't do much better."},{"time":171000,"text":"Last year, Pew and the Colombia J-School analyzed the 14,000 stories"},{"time":176000,"text":"that appeared on Google News' front page."},{"time":179000,"text":"And they, in fact, covered the same 24 news events."},{"time":183000,"text":"Similarly, a study in e-content showed that much of global news from U.S. news creators"},{"time":188000,"text":"is recycled stories from the AP wire services and Reuters,"},{"time":192000,"text":"and don't put things into a context that people can understand their connection to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196000,"text":"So, if you put it all together, this could help explain why today's college graduates,"},{"time":201000,"text":"as well as less educated Americans,"},{"time":203000,"text":"know less about the world than their counterparts did 20 years ago."},{"time":206000,"text":"And if you think it's simply because we are not interested,"},{"time":212000,"text":"you would be wrong."},{"time":214000,"text":"In recent years, Americans who say they closely follow global news most of the time"},{"time":221000,"text":"grew to over 50 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223000,"text":"The real question: is this distorted worldview what we want for Americans"},{"time":231000,"text":"in our increasingly interconnected world?"},{"time":234000,"text":"I know we can do better."},{"time":237000,"text":"And can we afford not to? Thank you."}]}]}